Dialogue: 5,0:22:05.22,0:22:07.57,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, let's make that call.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:07.57,0:22:09.71,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The number's probably already programmed in.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.63,0:22:08.76,Phone,,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz17.462\pos(620,356)\clip(m 602 345 l 611 358 618 372 575 381 575 357)}Copy
Dialogue: 5,0:22:09.71,0:22:12.71,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,If we call from here, won't people think \NTaro Kawaguchi's come back to life?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:12.71,0:22:14.37,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No one remembers his number.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:14.37,0:22:16.07,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But if you don't want \Nto, use your cell phone.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:18.81,0:22:19.81,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What should I say?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:20.04,0:22:23.23,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,"I'd to submit a manuscript" or something.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:24.92,0:22:25.79,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm calling.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:25.79,0:22:27.32,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:31.80,0:22:33.79,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Shonen Jack editorial department.
